ğŸ’» Types of Hackers
âš« Black Hat Hackers (Bad Hackers)
Illegal hackers who break into systems for personal gain, money, or malicious intent.
They steal data, spread malware, or damage systems â€” all without permission.
Example: A hacker who steals credit card data or leaks private information.

âšª White Hat Hackers (Good Hackers)
Also called Ethical Hackers.
They hack with permission to help organizations find and fix vulnerabilities.
Often part of Red Teams or security testing groups.
Example: A cybersecurity professional who tests a companyâ€™s website for weaknesses to make it safer.

âš«âšª Gray Hat Hackers (In Between)
Hack without permission but not always for harm.
They might find a bug and tell the company â€” but since they accessed it without approval, itâ€™s still technically illegal.
Example: A hacker who discovers a flaw in a bankâ€™s website and reports it, but didnâ€™t get approval first.

